How to install advwall on a GNU/Linux system :

- Clone the git repo into /usr/src
- Symlink /usr/src/advwall/etc/advwall to /etc/advwall
- Symlink /usr/src/advwall/etc/init.d/advwall.sh to /etc/init.d/advwall
- Configure your rules
- Test them (be careful with local rules, USE THE TIMER!)
- Remove the backups made with the tests
- Add it to the boot process.


How to uninstall it :

- Stop it
- Remove it from the boot process
- Remove /etc/advwall and /etc/init.d/advwall
- Done.


How to submit a bug :

Send a email to r.meillon@servitics.fr




Thanks using it !